SIMPLE: unhang
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unhang
<hw>Un*hang"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>hang</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To divest or strip of hangings; to remove the
hangings, as a room.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To remove (something hanging or swinging) from that
which supports it; <as>as, to <ex>unhang</ex> a gate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unhap</ent>⟦br⟧
